EDITORS COMMENTS

In this print captured by Baz Ratner, we witness a serene moment as a man gracefully paddles through the tranquil waters of the Yarkon river in Tel Aviv, Israel. The image, taken on October 31,2016, showcases the beauty and serenity that can be found amidst the bustling cityscape. The composition is simply breathtaking; with soft sunlight filtering through scattered clouds above, casting a warm glow upon the water's surface. The man appears to be completely at ease as he navigates his way through the gentle currents. His paddle slices smoothly into the water, creating ripples that delicately disturb its calmness. This photograph serves as a reminder of nature's ability to provide solace and escape from our daily routines. Amidst Tel Aviv's vibrant urban landscape, where modernity often takes center stage, it is refreshing to see someone embracing nature so intimately. The Yarkon river itself holds historical significance for Tel Aviv residents and visitors alike. It has witnessed countless stories unfold along its banks throughout time. In this particular moment frozen in time by Ratner's lens, we are granted an opportunity to reflect upon our own connection with nature and appreciate its timeless allure. Ratner's skillful capture invites us to pause and contemplate life's simple pleasures – those moments when we can find solace within ourselves while immersed in nature’s embrace.
